implementation

Class CourseDescription

  • java.lang.Object
    • implementation.CourseDescription

  • public class CourseDescription
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a single course offered by ACU. Maintains data for
    • CRN (course registration number)
    • course subject
    • course title
    • course number

    Instances of CourseDescription will also contain CRNs, by which Courses may look up data from their coresponding CourseDescription.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Kevin Shurtz

      • CourseDescription

        public CourseDescription(int crnNum,
                         java.lang.String subject,
                         int courseNum,
                         java.lang.String title)
        Constructs a Course object to represent a student's course. Course delegates the instantiation of instance variables to method setCourse.
        Parameters:
        crnNum - course registration number
        subject - course subject, such as 'BIBL', 'CS', 'IT', etc
        title - course title, such as 'Software Engineering', 'Networking', etc
        courseNum - course number, such as 220, 221, etc
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If one of the arguements provided was unacceptable
        See Also:
        setCourseDescription(int, String, int, String)

      • setCourseCRN

        public void setCourseCRN(int crnNum)
        Assigns the course registration number. No validation is conducted.
        Parameters:
        crnNum - course registration number, a unique course identifier

      • setCourseSubject

        public void setCourseSubject(java.lang.String subject)
        Assigns the course subject. No validation is conducted on the string, but typically a course subject is fully capitalized, and no longer than four characters.
        Parameters:
        subject - course subject, such as BIBL, CS, IT, etc

      • setCourseNumber

        public void setCourseNumber(int courseNum)
        Assigns the course number. Examples include 101, 102, 374, etc. Extensions to course numbers, like 'H1' in '101.H1', are not stored in this field. Rather, extensions are stored as a String in setCourseNumberExt. If a course number does not consist of three digits, an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        courseNum - course number
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the course number is not three digits
        See Also:
        Course.setCourseNumberExt(String)

      • setCourseTitle

        public void setCourseTitle(java.lang.String title)
        Assigns the course title. No validation is conducted. The title is not to include the course's number, or other identifying information.
        Parameters:
        title - the title of the course, such as 'Software Engineering', or 'Networking'
